text: Where are you trying to run this code?
Does event.object.objectId have a value inside of it?

Hi In that custom workflow from the other day that I was looking for the latest associated calls and (separately) emails. Yes the <http://event.object.it|event.object.objectId > has the correct client record id value.

If I just ask it to return console.log(searchCustomResponse) it returns [object object].

After this I used the APIv4 url to call the contact-emails and contact-calls associations and that worked as expected. Can you add a sort request in that url to make it appear in descending order of creation? Thanks

oh ok, yeah so you posted this in <#CFPRTEGTX|modules> which is for website modules not workflow actions I was a little confused. you'll want to use `event.fields.objectId`  instead of event.object.objectId

OK good to know on the channels.

That returned: Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'objectId')
